post_text: Minster Schools are planning to start school on Wed. Aug. 26 as scheduled. We plan to have in-person instruction five days a week for all students. The school is developing a plan that will include many precautions to keep the students and staff safe next year. Parents were sent an email today with more information and a link to a survey asking for feedback to help us in developing the plan. Please complete the survey by July 15. We will be working closely with the Auglaize County Health Department to start the school year as normally and safely as possible.

post_text: From our resident lab worker Mrs. Bruns. Please consider helping the cause...
shared_text:
Marianne Wuebker Bruns
March 20 at 9:03 AM ¬∑

PLEASE PLEASE PLEASE CONSIDER sharing this on your feed and donating!! I just got the following message from my boss at the lab: Marianne- please help spread the word to your students.... I want you to pass on to everyone you know that this nation is in dire need of blood donations. Please consider donating yourself and bringing a friend or two along. For Versailles Troy area you will need to look at the Community Blood Center website. I know there are drives in Sidney and Troy next week. For Indiana you will want to look at either American Red Cross or Indiana Blood Center for your closest drive. We need red cells and platelets urgently!

I want you to pass on to everyone you know that this nation is in dire need of blood donations. Please consider donating yourself and bringing a friend or two along. For Versailles Troy area you will need to look at the Community Blood Center website. I know there are drives in Sidney and Troy next week. For Indiana you will want to look at either American Red Cross or Indiana Blood Center for your closest drive. We need red cells and platelets urgently!

This Friday night (January 17), the varsity basketball team will host Marion Local on OHSAA Military Appreciation Night. All veterans and active-duty military will receive free admission to the game, and veteran relatives of all varsity players and coaches (for both teams) will be introduced as honorary captains prior to the game. Additionally, the Wildcat pep band will play military-themed songs throughout the evening. We encourage students from both schools to wear red, white and blue to show their support.

The JV contest tips at 6pm. We hope to see you there!

post_text: The Minster YAE (You Are Enough) members have the opportunity to earn $200 if they have at least 20 adults (must be 21 or older and reside in Allen, Auglaize, or Hardin county) complete an 8 hour (2 X 4 hour sessions) mental health first aid training. Mental Health First Aid is an evidence-based, globally recognized program designed to teach parents, family members, caregivers, teachers, school staff, peers, neighbors, health and human services workers, and other caring citizens how to help an individual who is experiencing mental health distress. The training will be provided by Prevention Awareness Support Services (PASS) and The Mental Health and Recovery Services Board of Allen,‚Ä¶ More
